info: Rating, 5 stars,  · March 2024,  · Stayed a few nights
rating_comment: Very friendly staff, location somewhat far from downtown but in a very nice environment. Very comfortable room. The cleanliness was not ideal, but nothing serious, evidently in these countries what is impeccable for them is not for Westerners. The breakfast was alright. It's overpriced

info: Rating, 5 stars,  · February 2022,  · Stayed over a week
rating_comment: One of the best addresses in Dhaka where you can feel a wolf. Although I'm a native of Bangladeshi, I live on my Bangladesh trips, at least in Dhaka in a hotel because I'm independent. Hotel Dhaka Golden Inn, in Banani is now my favorite. There is still old furniture in the rooms, but everything is tip top clean. The towels and linens are fresh. The staff is competent, always helpful and very friendly and does not always hold your hand for a tip. I get back in here when I'm in Dhaka.

info: Rating, 5 stars,  · February 2022,  · Stayed about a week
rating_comment: It’s definitely worth it.All stuffs are very helpful & accommodating. They are very scrupulous about your need to make your stay nice. Prices are way cheaper that even includes breakfast, that made me surprised.Definitely recommend & I will stay back again.
